Publication bias in meta-analyses was examined using four indices: 1) Egger's test (Egger et al., 1997); 2) the Begg and Mazumdar rank (Begg and Mazumdar, 1994); 3) Duval and Tweedie's trim-and-fill (Duval and Tweedie, 2000); and 4) the leave-one-out ‘jack-knife’ sensitivity analysis (Sinharay, 2010).Results
A flow chart summarizing the literature search process is presented in Fig. 1.
